Official Documentation : https://docs.flowiseai.com/getting-started
Version : 1.4.3

Flowise is an open-source low-code/no-code tool to build LLM (Large Language Model) apps and workflows.
Think of it as a drag-and-drop builder for LangChain pipelines, chatbots, RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) systems, and agent workflows.

üîπ Flowise Usage
1. Chatbot / Q&A Systems

Build chatbots that connect to OpenAI, Anthropic, Llama, HuggingFace models.

Add memory to maintain context across conversations.

Can be embedded into websites or apps.

Example: Customer support chatbot that answers from your company‚Äôs docs.

2. RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)

Connects LLMs with vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate, Qdrant, Milvus, ChromaDB, etc.).

Lets you upload documents (PDF, CSV, Notion, Confluence, etc.) and query them in natural language.

Example: Upload financial reports ‚Üí ask ‚ÄúWhat was the revenue growth in Q2 2024?‚Äù
